cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on anomaly detection for moving cognitive agents in a given environment. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper uses both external and private first-person visual observations to characterize agents' motion. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the proposed method uses Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) to produce an estimation of external and internal parameters of moving agents. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the proposed method trains the GANs in a semi-unsupervised way. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also relevant as the paper deals with self-aware embodied agents and their motion in a given environment.
